Where do I start... This year has definitely been the most insane and most defining. A year after my first BFA, I stand here again a 10000 times more confident, more comfortable. Sitting in a room with people I admire so much, an experience I’ve dreamed of since I was a little. I can only say this made me realise how hard I want to work and make my mark in this industry that’s so amazing but could do with so much change. Watching @adutakech win the award for model of the year just shows that anything is possible. I’m thinking there is a possibility that a trans model will be nominated in the next couple of years, we can only hope. I want to thank my amazing team who work around the clock to get me everywhere @mannyuk @archnasawjani @bravemodels. The girls who changed my life forever @chaos, who believed in me to deliver and took me under their wing when I was going through a tough time. It’s been an amazing year. Let’s get it, I’m so ready for everything that’s still coming my way. Thank you @katespadeny & @nicola_glass for this look and for the great dinner company. @joeyjoeychoy & @carl.campbelll for the sickening beat. Remember, everything happens for a reason and Rome wasn’t built in a day!

Don’t let anyone ever tell you that you’re not good enough: not intelligent, pretty, sexy enough. You can achieve anything you put your mind to. I’ve come a LONG way to be here today. I can’t even count how many times I’ve been told I won’t come across as a “natural” woman. What the hell does that even mean, and why should it matter, because I feel hella like a woman. Everything that happened to me, every time I thought of giving up, and then realised I’ve come so far; those moments got me to where I am today. We’ve all fought battles. Be proud of your journey. Share your journey, SHOW IT OFF. You are a STAR. I LOVE YOU. #TRANSISBEAUTIFUL

This is me, at the European Parliament, wearing a dress made of flags from the 75 (now 72 💃🏻) countries around the world, where it is illegal to be a part of the LGBTQ+ community. I will re-post this picture, as long as it’s necessary. Slowly but surely, we are making progress. I don’t wish it upon anyone in this position to be hurt, simply because they are living their truth. As a privileged member of the community, I urge everyone who is privileged to keep fighting for those who cant speak up. Never forget to keep dreaming and believing in yourself and the world, no matter how dark it gets sometimes. 🦋

(There are still 72 countries where it is illegal to be LGBTQ+)The fact that there are governments actively thinking about how they can punish their citizens for being a part of the LGBTQ+ community, is sickening. 
Some of these countries have set in place legal consequences for those who decide they don’t want to hide who they are. Some being imprisonment for life, some the death penalty. 
My heart goes out for those, who are stuck in these places, and are forced to live a reality that’s not theirs. I feel conflicted by travelling to these places, no only because I don’t want to support the government, but also because I fear for my own safety. 
I grew up, learning about other cultures from a young age. I was very privileged to be in a position where this was possible and I could visit and appreciate other parts of the world. 
I would love to travel to some of these places because a government is not always a reflection of the population, but sadly I would be refused entry to many of the countries on the list. 
When people close to me tell me they still go to hotels owned by the sultan of brunei, go to equinox & soul cycle, and use facilities from other organisations that are supporting anti LGBTQ+ groups, it saddens me. They will argue with me, because they don’t understand how it affects me personally. But next time you go to one of these places, remember your lunch, dinner, hotel stay, etc. funds governments and organisations that want ME, your friend, and my community erased. 
I understand that if you’re not in a minority, you will never understand the struggle, but you can be an ally, listen, and educate yourself. TO NOT UNDERSTAND is one thing. TO ACTIVELY GO AGAINST ONE’S LIFE, is another. 
Be safe everyone, 
Much love, 
Maxim
